Class TextBuilder

java.lang.Object
io.github.sosuisen.jfxbuilder.graphics.TextBuilder
public class TextBuilder extends Object
The TextBuilder class constructs instances of the Text class and offers a fluent interface for creating and configuring it.

This class includes a static create method that accepts the same arguments as the original Text constructor and returns an instance of the TextBuilder.

You can use method chaining to call the builder methods for configuring the Text. Finally, invoke the build method to generate an instance of the Text class.

Note that intermediate builder methods are not evaluated until the build method is called, meaning they are evaluated lazily.

Author:
Hidekazu Kubota <hidekazu.kubota@gmail.com>
